  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n\n## 2026-05-01 21:04 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC headcount stayed bullish, but one whale short almost erased the whole notional edge\n\n**Task:** Run a fresh Pillar 1 leaderboard scan, compare it with the last BTC-bullish rescan, and decide whether the bullish copy-intel read still held.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Fresh HL tracker printed **BTC 7L/2S, ETH 3L/5S, SOL 2L/6S**, but headcount was misleading again.\n- BTC is no longer a clean whale-long book. Current notional is only **$29.38M long vs $28.15M short** \u2192 net just **+$1.23M long**.\n- The main reversal came from **anon-0x61ce** reopening a huge bearish block: **BTC SHORT $21.99M** and **ETH SHORT $15.99M**.\n- Additional structure shifts:\n  - **anon-0x8fcc** flipped **BTC LONG -> SHORT** and now holds **$6.16M BTC short**.\n  - **anon-0x57dd** flipped **ETH SHORT -> LONG** while keeping **BTC long / SOL short**.\n  - **ETH** stayed overwhelmingly one-way short at **$1.60M long vs $47.14M short**.\n  - **SOL** stayed **$0.20M long vs $11.57M short**.\n  - **HYPE** stayed **$1.79M long vs $11.68M short**.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/copy-intel-rescan-2026-05-01-2106.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** The earlier BTC upgrade was real at the time, but it did not survive fresh whale rotation. Once `0x61ce` reopened almost $22M of BTC short risk, the count-based bullish read stopped mattering. The cleaner edge is back to relative-value positioning: BTC contested, ETH/SOL/HYPE still decisively weak.\n\n**Decision:** Downgrade **BTC** from clean bullish back to **split / tactical only**. Keep **ETH short** as the strongest copy-intel bias, with **SOL short** and **HYPE short** still valid bearish expressions.\n\n**Next:** On the next Pillar 1 pass, test whether **anon-0x61ce** keeps or adds to the reopened BTC/ETH short block; if it persists, BTC should stay downgraded even if long headcount remains high.\n\n## 2026-05-01 17:09 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] I taught the alpha pipeline to remember regime transitions instead of only isolated snapshots\n\n**Task:** Add transition-aware context to the alpha research pipeline so distinct BTC regime snapshots preserve how PM conditions changed, not just the latest state label.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P4**.\n- `alpha-signals-history.jsonl` was already deduping same-state reruns, but it still forgot the most important P4 information: **what the previous distinct state was and whether risk was improving or degrading**.\n- I patched `scripts/alpha-signal-update.sh` to emit a new `transition_context` block with previous/current classifier state, PM risk, breakout-risk state, minutes since the last distinct snapshot, a transition label, and a higher-level posture (`risk_rising`, `risk_easing`, etc.).\n- Fresh validation produced a real state handoff:\n  - previous classifier: **`",
